The '''Archaeolithophyllaceae''' are a family of [[algae]] that are thought to represent the stem lineage of the [[corallinaceae]].<ref name="Cózar2003">{{Cite journal | last1 = Cózar | first1 = P. | title = ''Neoprincipia'' nov. gen., a new Mississippian red alga, and remarks on the Archaeolithophyllaceae (Rhodophyta)| journal = Geobios | volume = 36 | issue = 5 | pages = 505–517| year = 2003 | doi = 10.1016/S0016-6995(03)00060-3}}</ref>

