'''Lamberto II da Polenta''' (died 1347) was briefly jointly lord of [[Ravenna]] and [[Cervia]] from 1346 until his death.

He was the son of [[Ostasio I da Polenta]]. In 1346 he inherited the family lordships together with his brothers [[Bernardino I da Polenta|Bernardino I]] and [[Pandolfo da Polenta|Pandolfo]]. Bernardino, however, had both Pandolfo and Lamberto imprisoned in Cervia after one year, where they died of starvation.

