{{spanish name|Maureira|Riquelme}} {{use dmy dates|date=September 2015}}
{{Infobox person |name = Valentina Maureira |image = Valentina Maureira.jpg |alt = |caption = |birth_name = Valentina Maureira Riquelme |birth_date = 2000/01 |birth_place = [[Chile]] |death_date = {{Death date and age|2015|5|14|2001|1|1|df=y}} |death_place = [[Pontifical Catholic University of Chile]], [[Santiago]], [[Chile]] |death_cause = [[Cystic fibrosis]] |other_names = |known_for = [[Euthanasia]] plea to Chilean President, [[Michelle Bachelet]] |occupation = |parents = Fredy Maureira |nationality = Chilean |website = }}
'''Valentina Maureira Riquelme''' (2000/01 – May 14, 2015) was a Chilean teenager who gained international attention after using [[social media]] to ask Chilean President [[Michele Bachelet]] to allow her to die by [[euthanasia]]. Bachelet denied her request.<ref name="inquisitr.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.inquisitr.com/1891015/valentina-maureira-president-responds-to-teenagers-euthanasia-request/|title=Valentina Maureira: President Responds To Teenager's Euthanasia Request|date=3 March 2015|work=The Inquisitr News|accessdate=17 May 2015}}</ref>
==Biography== Maureira was the daughter of Freddy Maureira and had a brother who died at the age of six of [[cystic fibrosis]]. She was herself diagnosed with the disease shortly afterwards.<ref name="inquisitr.com"/>
Early in 2015, she used [[YouTube]] to post a video asking President Bachelet to allow her to be [[Euthanasia|euthanised]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.news.com.au/lifestyle/health/cystic-fibrosis-sufferer-valentina-maureira-fails-in-euthanasia-plea-to-chile-president-michelle-bachelet/story-fneuzlbd-1227240961852|title=Cystic fibrosis sufferer Valentina Maureira’s euthanasia plea fails|date=27 February 2015|work=NewsComAu|accessdate=17 May 2015}}</ref> Bachelet denied the request based on Chile's laws, citing the Catholicism in their country as a reason to enforce those laws.
Days later, President Bachelet visited the stricken girl in the hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/mar/01/chile-president-michelle-bachelet-valentina-maureira-cystic-fibrosis-euthanasia-video|title=Chile president visits girl with cystic fibrosis who posted euthanasia video|date=28 February 2015|work=the Guardian|accessdate=17 May 2015}}</ref> Up until 23 March, Maureira received public support for her wellbeing and met someone aged beyond 20 with similar disease, prompting her to change her mind about euthanasia.<ref>{{cite web|author=Lucy Sherriff Multimedia editor, The Huffington Post UK |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2015/03/23/teen-euthanasia-changes-mind-public-support_n_6922440.html |title=Valentina Maureira, 14, Changes Her Mind About Wanting Euthanasia After Outpouring Of Public Support |publisher=The Huffington Post |date=2015-03-23 |accessdate=2017-04-08}}</ref>
On 14 May, Maureira died at age 14 in the hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/news/latino/chilean-girl-who-asked-president-let-her-die-passes-away-n359486 |title=Chilean Girl Who Asked To Be Allowed To Die Passes Away |publisher=NBC News |date= |accessdate=2017-04-08}}</ref>
